com.m87.sdk
Interface ProximityManager.Callbacks

Enclosing class:
ProximityManager
public static interface ProximityManager.Callbacks

Defines the interface used to send events to the application.

The app must implement this interface and pass it to the SDK upon initialization. The SDK will then call the corresponding method when an event occurs.

This interface is used to send both solicited (i.e. by the app) events (e.g. onInitialize, onPublish, etc.) and unsolicited (i.e. from MWC) events (i.e. onEvent) to the application.
